>Can we put primitive type int[] ... as parameter instead of custom Class, make it look like a pure mathematical function, like abs, min, max. Let service consumer decide which metric and duration should be calculated?

`int[]...` looks like a two-dimensional matrix. by using that, you need to explain which dimensional is using for a sample list, and which one is for timeline. You just leave the explanation to document, still there. Personally, this baseline is more than a library, it is a module for collector. Explicit `class` names are still my choice.

@peng-yongsheng thought?

The role of baseline is a module of collector but not a utils. So, I suggest the services of this module should be done explicit jobs that just happen in APM system. 
The method and args looks like: 
minuteBaseLineCompute(MinuteMetric[] minuteMetric);

This issue cause by weaved the Controller code. The Skywalking agent generate another constructor if the class has interceptor constructor.  and Spring create bean instance by default constructor if the bean has multi constructors.

Here is the code of spring class `org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.AutowiredAnnotationBeanPostProcessor`
```
if (candidateConstructors == null) {
      ..... 
} else if (rawCandidates.length == 1 && rawCandidates[0].getParameterTypes().length > 0) {
     candidateConstructors = new Constructor<?>[] {rawCandidates[0]};
} else {
     candidateConstructors = new Constructor<?>[0];
}
```

I mean what ever Response Time, Total Calls and Error Calls all have exactly same data struct.
like that:
`Class RespTimeInMinuteOfSingleDay{
    private int[] resp;
}
Class TotalCallInMinuteOfSingleDay{
    private int[] calls;
}
`
At the code implementation level, may be they share the same parent class, and nothing in subclass.
